summary: In this context, 1,1,2-trichloroethene (TCE) is mentioned as a chlorinated volatile organic compound (VOC) that undergoes degradation in the hyporheic zone, while dichlorobis(ethylenediamine)rhodium(III) is not directly referenced or discussed in relation to TCE.
